<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Trash1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Trash,</orth> subst. worthless matter, dross, lumber: <cit><quote>it is but t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.223" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 223</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lay hands upon these traitors and their t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 44</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 157</bibl>. Used of worthless persons: <cit><quote>this poor t. of Venice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.312" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 312</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I do suspect this t. to be a party in this injury,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 85</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>